XSSer
Automatic XSS vulnerability detection framework

Web Application
Description
XSSer is an automatic framework to detect, exploit and report XSS vulnerabilities in web applications.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which xsser
Install command:

sudo apt install xsser
Basic Syntax
xsser -u "<URL>"
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
xsser -u "http://target.com/search?q=test"

Basic XSS test	Test for reflected XSS	
xsser -u "http://target.com/search?q=test" --auto

Auto mode	Automatic payload selection	
xsser -u "http://target.com/search?q=test" --Fp "<script>alert(1)</script>"

Custom payload	Test specific payload	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Find input parameters
2
Run xsser against target
3
Review injection results
4
Test successful payloads manually
5
Document XSS findings
Understanding the Output
Shows tested payloads and successful injections. Color-coded results.

Important Warnings
•
XSS can steal user sessions
•
Test only on authorized apps
•
Some payloads may be blocked by WAF
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
